HEADWORD: Neuroma
<hw>Neu*ro"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Neuro-</er>, and <er>-oma</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
tumor developed on, or connected with, a nerve, esp. one consisting of
new-formed nerve fibers.</def>⟦br⟧
